headline: Starbucks appoints first China chief growth officer - media
summary: Starbucks China has appointed its first Chief Growth Officer (CGO), Chinese media outlet Late Post reported on Tuesday. The media outlet said the company has hired Tony Yang, former partner and president of digital marketing firm Tezign, to the role. The U.S. coffee giant and Tezign did not immediately respond to Reuters' request for comment.

headline: Police Find UnitedHealth Shooting Suspect in McDonald’s: ‘We Knew That Was Our Guy’
summary: Luigi Mangione, a 26-year-old Ivy League graduate who worked in tech, was arrested in Pennsylvania. He was charged with felony weapons and forgery offenses.
